  "summary": "Dependency-confusion recon beacon exfiltrates host data and /etc/passwd at install time",
  "details": "package.json declares `\"preinstall\": \"node index.js\"`, which fires automatically on `npm install`. index.js collects host identifiers (os.hostname, os.userInfo, homedir, DNS servers) and reads sensitive system files (/etc/passwd, /etc/hosts) plus package metadata, then HTTPS POSTs the bundle to a hardcoded Burp Collaborator subdomain `hzklpyrf8gdhgtycz16veroqihobc10q.oastify.com`. The package ships no real functionality — empty description, empty author, and a name resembling a plausible internal Trello/ConfigCat integration — fingerprint of a dependency-confusion squat whose only purpose is to beacon installer-side data to the attacker for follow-on targeting.",
